proposal.description:
JoystreamStats runs 10 websocket endpoints accessible at `pioneer.joystreamstats.live`. Using `testnet.joystream.org`
- click on the upper left circle
- activate `custom endpoint`
- enter `wss://joystreamstats.live:9945`
- push `Save & Reload`

The bounty can be reviewed here: https://github.com/Joystream/community-repo/issues/101

# Specs and location

All nodes have at least 2GB RAM and are well connected.

Asia
- Sydney (Australia)
- Mumbai (India)
- Singapore
- Tokyo (Japan)

Europe
- Gravelines (France)
- Helsinki (Finland)
- London (United Kingdom)
- Nuremberg (Germany)
- Warsaw (Poland)

North America:
- Beauharnois (Canada)

Since the main server `joystreamstats.live` is hosted in Germany latency may improve accessing a nearby mirror directly:
`wss://CITY.api.joystreamstats.live/endpoint`

# Configs and flags (node)

Requests to `joystreamstats:9945` are balanced among above nodes via nginx upstream. Nodes are run by systemd with following arguments:
`joystream-node --chain joy-testnet-4.json --pruning archive --validator --name CITY.api.joystreamstats.live --rpc-cors all`

If you are interested to try a similar setup, these nginx snippets may help:

Main node:
```
upstream endpoint {
         server $subdomain:443;
}
server {
    listen 9945 ssl;
    server_name $domain;

    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/$domain/fullchain.pem; #managed by Certbot
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/$domain/privkey.pem; # managed by Certbot
    include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem; # managed by Certbot

    location / {
      proxy_pass https://endpoint/endpoint;
      proxy_http_version 1.1;
      proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
      proxy_set_header Connection "Upgrade";
      proxy_set_header Host $host;
      proxy_set_header    X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }
}

Mirror:
```
server {
    listen 80;
    return 301 https://$subdomain$request_uri;
}
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name $subdomain;

    location /endpoint {
      proxy_pass  http://localhost:9944;
      proxy_http_version 1.1;
      proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
      proxy_set_header Connection "Upgrade";
      proxy_set_header Host $host;
      proxy_set_header    X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }
    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/$subdomain/fullchain.pem; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/$subdomain/privkey.pem; # managed by Certbot
    include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem; # managed by Certbot
}
```

